[1] Texas (Bell County)
Date: Mon 19 Mar 2012
Source: KXXV [edited]
http://www.kxxv.com/story/17193198/whooping-cough-becoming-a-growing-concern-in-bell-county


More cases of whooping cough have been confirmed in the Bell County area. As of Monday, 19 Mar 2012, there are 14 confirmed cases in both Belton and Temple, with 8 probable cases that have yet to be confirmed. The health department is expecting more cases to surface. While the cases are, for the most part, not connected, it is still vital to recognize symptoms early.

