[4] Washington (Kittitas County)
Date: Fri 16 Mar 2012
Source: KNDO [edited]
http://www.kndo.com/story/17179334/more-cases-of-pertussis-in-kittitas-county


2 more cases of pertussis, or whooping cough, have been confirmed in Kittitas County. Health officials say one child is home schooled while the other is a student at Damman School.

The Health Department says anyone who is not up-to-date on their whooping cough vaccines should not visit Damman School for 21 days, as a precaution.

This is the 3rd pertussis case in Kittitas County in 2012 and 8 people have been hospitalized in Washington state already in 2012.

[Byline: Aaron Hilf]

