[6] New York (Tompkins County)
Date: Wed 14 Mar 2012
Source: The Ithaca Journal [edited]
http://www.theithacajournal.com/article/20120314/NEWS01/203140327/Tompkins-Health-Department-targets-whooping-cough-through-prevention-education?odyssey=tab%7Ctopnews%7Ctext%7CFRONTPAGE


With a recent increase in whooping cough cases, the Tompkins County Health Department is focusing efforts to educate the public to contain the disease. "There are more cases than we saw in all of 2011," Tompkins County Public Health Director Frank Kruppa said Tuesday, 13 Mar 2012.

As of 13 Mar 2011, there were 15 pertussis cases recorded in 2012, 2 more than in all of 2011. The disease normally occurs more frequently in the winter, although cases can happen any time of year.

